04/04/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Macedonia was set to join the World Trade Organisation (WTO) on Friday (4 April), following nearly ten years of negotiations. On 5 March, Skopje advised the international trade body that its parliament had ratified the protocol that lays out the terms and conditions for membership. A candidate country is admitted 30 days after ratification. Macedonia becomes the 146th member of the WTO and the third country from the former Yugoslavia, behind Slovenia and Croatia. (AP, AFP - 03/04/03)
